@description.name: @description
@description.body: Define a new class using the qooxdoo class system. Lightweight version of {@link qx.Class#define} with less features.

@param.name: @param
@param.body:
name {String?} Name of the class. If null, the class will not be
   attached to a namespace.
@param.description:
Name of the class. If null, the class will not be
   attached to a namespace.

@param.name: @param
@param.body:
config {Map ? null} Class definition structure. The configuration map has the following keys:
NameTypeDescription
extendClassThe super class the current class inherits from.
constructFunctionThe constructor of the class.
staticsMapMap of static values / functions of the class.
membersMapMap of instance members of the class.
deferFunctionFunction that is called at the end of processing the class declaration.
@param.description:
Class definition structure. The configuration map has the following keys:
NameTypeDescription
extendClassThe super class the current class inherits from.
constructFunctionThe constructor of the class.
staticsMapMap of static values / functions of the class.
membersMapMap of instance members of the class.
deferFunctionFunction that is called at the end of processing the class declaration.

@description.name: @description
@description.body: Executes the defer methods for classes which are required by the dependency information in dbClassInfo (which is a map in the format generated by qxcompiler). Defer methods are of course only executed once but they are always put off until absolutely necessary to avoid potential side effects and recursive and/or difficult to resolve dependencies.

@param.name: @param
@param.body: dbClassInfo {Object} qxcompiler map
@param.description: qxcompiler map

@description.name: @description
@description.body:
Returns a function whose "this" is altered. Syntax 

qx.Bootstrap.bind(myFunction, [self, [varargs...]]);

Example 

 function myFunction()
 {
   this.setStyle('color', 'red');


 };
 var myBoundFunction = qx.Bootstrap.bind(myFunction, myElement);
 myBoundFunction();

@param.name: @param

@param.description: Original function to wrap

@param.description: The object that the "this" of the function will refer to.

@param.body: varargs {arguments ? null} The arguments to pass to the function.
@param.description: The arguments to pass to the function.
